description: Lists all tags currently on a named resource. A tag is a key-value pair where the key and value are case-sensitive. You can use tags to categorize and track your MemoryDB resources. For more information, see Tagging your MemoryDB resources. When you add or remove tags from multi region clusters, you might not immediately see the latest effective tags in the ListTags API response due to it being eventually consistent specifically for multi region clusters. For more information, see Tagging your MemoryDB resources.

parameters.name: ResourceArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource for which you want the list of tags.

nested_items.name: TagList
nested_items.description: A list of tags as key-value pairs.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The key for the tag. May not be null.

nested_items.name: Value
nested_items.description: The tag's value. May be null.
